    {
      "kind": "mentions",
      "mentions": [
        "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/checking-the-pixel-format-of-a-postprocess-effect-s-output-texture",
        "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/implementing-postprocess-effects-using-metal-compute-functions",
        "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/using-metal-performance-shaders-to-create-custom-postprocess-effects"
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In iOS 15 and later, as well as macOS 12 and later, you can register a callback function to apply",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "postprocessing effects to RealityKit’s rendered scene. Once every frame, RealityKit calls that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "function before it displays the scene. You can use this callback to apply postprocess effects using",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "any APIs that can modify an image texture. However, because RealityKit calls this method every",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "frame, you should only use APIs that execute on the GPU, such as Metal compute functions,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metalperformanceshaders",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ",",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreimage",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". You can also render additional",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "content, such as a rendered SpriteKit scene, on top of the frame buffer.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "For more information on implementing postprocess effects, see",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/realitykit/implementing_special_rendering_effects_with_realitykit_postprocessing",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ",",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "which demonstrates multiple postprocess techniques.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A postprocess callback takes a single ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "PostProcessContext",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter, which contains",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "data the callback function needs to modify the rendered scene, including the frame buffer, depth",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "map, and a property for writing the modified image. If you’ve registered a postprocess callback,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that function needs to encode to the output texture or the frame is never displayed.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A postprocess function looks like this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "    func myPostProcessCallback(context: ARView.PostProcessContext) {",
            "        // Handle postprocessing here.",
            "    }"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To register a function as the postprocess render callback, assign it to the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView/RenderCallbacks-swift.struct/postProcess",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property of the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView/renderCallbacks-swift.property",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": "  property of the scene’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "ARView",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ":",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "arView.renderCallbacks.postProcess = myPostProcessCallback"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To stop postprocessing, set the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView/RenderCallbacks-swift.struct/postProcess",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "render callback to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "nil",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "arView.renderCallbacks.postProcess = nil"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If your app turns postprocessing on and off frequently, another option for disabling postprocess",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "effects is to keep your callback registered, but use an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Metal/MTLBlitCommandEncoder",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to encode the unmodified framebuffer directly to the output texture whenever postprocess effects",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "aren’t active.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            " func myPostProcessCallback(context: ARView.PostProcessContext) {",
            "     if (usePostProcessEffects) {",
            "         handlePostProcessing(context: ARView.PostProcessContext)",
            "         return",
            "     }",
            "",
            "",
            "     // If postprocess effects are disabled, copy sourceColorTexture",
            "     // directly to targetColorTexture.",
            "     let blitEncoder = context.commandBuffer.makeBlitCommandEncoder()",
            "     blitEncoder?.copy(from: context.sourceColorTexture, to: context.targetColorTexture)",
            "     blitEncoder?.endEncoding()",
            " }"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
